630
00:51:08,160 --> 00:51:12,517
Tell me honestly, are you dating me
just so you can win the case?

631
00:51:12,600 --> 00:51:16,798
What about you?
Are you seeing me for the same reason?

632
00:51:18,120 --> 00:51:21,271
l really don't care about winning the case.

633
00:51:21,360 --> 00:51:24,909
When l lose one, l'll win another.
l get paid either way.

634
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:28,595
A good girlfriend is different.
l haven't met one in ten years.

635
00:51:28,680 --> 00:51:32,593
When l met the right one,
she could have been spoken for.

636
00:51:33,320 --> 00:51:37,871
A good man is hard to come by too.
Most good men are married.

637
00:51:40,520 --> 00:51:43,193
Don't stare at me. You're not a good man.

638
00:51:43,280 --> 00:51:44,918
Because l'm not married?

639
00:51:51,040 --> 00:51:52,792
Are you all right?

640
00:51:52,880 --> 00:51:55,838
lt's just a kiss. Why the slap?

641
00:51:55,920 --> 00:51:58,514
lt just happened.
What do you want to do now?

642
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:02,875
Yes, it just happened.
What can l do now?

643
00:52:04,160 --> 00:52:05,115
l'm sorry.

644
00:52:08,040 --> 00:52:10,235
OK, you can slap me again.

645
00:52:10,320 --> 00:52:13,073
You can even pull a knife on me.

646
00:52:13,160 --> 00:52:14,309
Hit me one more time.

647
00:52:22,680 --> 00:52:25,558
lt's boring to catch your own fish.

648
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:30,673
The pleasure of fishing
doesn't depend on getting the fish...

649
00:52:30,760 --> 00:52:34,116
- lt depends on eating the fish?
- No.

650
00:52:34,200 --> 00:52:37,715
The time you spend
waiting patiently for the fish...

651
00:52:37,800 --> 00:52:41,634
That peace of mind you get
is pure pleasure.

652
00:52:41,720 --> 00:52:45,235
Why do fishermen
have so many wrinkles then?

653
00:52:45,320 --> 00:52:48,551
lf you're going to be difficult,
l won't talk to you.

654
00:53:01,800 --> 00:53:04,075
Have you thought of selling the fish farm?

655
00:53:04,160 --> 00:53:06,071
Why?

656
00:53:06,160 --> 00:53:10,039
Sell it and come to Australia with me.
We'll open a dairy farm there.

657
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:13,351
We'll spend our time milking the cows...

658
00:53:13,440 --> 00:53:17,638
Don't worry, we'll spend
most of our time on horseback,

659
00:53:17,720 --> 00:53:19,950
riding on the emerald pastures,

660
00:53:21,600 --> 00:53:23,875
looking out over the horizon.

661
00:53:23,960 --> 00:53:31,799
Riding over the mountains,
free like a floating cloud

662
00:53:31,880 --> 00:53:38,831
The freedom in the mountains
reflects peace in the city

663
00:53:38,920 --> 00:53:44,995
The beauty of the crescent moon

664
00:53:45,080 --> 00:53:47,992
Reflects peace in the city

665
00:53:49,040 --> 00:53:50,917
ls this a marriage proposal?

666
00:53:53,800 --> 00:53:57,236
Up to you. l'm an easy-going person.

667
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:03,230
- Can l tell you a secret?
- Yes.

668
00:54:04,680 --> 00:54:11,233
My father put it in his will that whoever
marries me will inherit the fish farm.

669
00:54:13,880 --> 00:54:16,440
Hey, why are you reacting this way?

670
00:54:18,320 --> 00:54:21,915
That's a big secret.
Now l've something serious to hide.

671
00:54:22,000 --> 00:54:24,309
l feel burdened by it.

672
00:54:25,120 --> 00:54:28,032
lmpossible, that's my secret.

673
00:54:29,040 --> 00:54:33,158
l'm not good at keeping things to myself.
l might blab it out one day.

674
00:54:33,240 --> 00:54:36,471
That's why l feel pressurised.

675
00:54:36,560 --> 00:54:38,596
Keep it like your own secret then.

676
00:54:38,680 --> 00:54:41,877
- My own secret?
- Yes.

677
00:54:44,360 --> 00:54:45,679
Do you feel better now?

678
00:54:48,200 --> 00:54:50,395
Yes, much better.

679
00:54:50,480 --> 00:54:54,029
lt feels different
to treat a secret as your own.

680
00:54:55,480 --> 00:55:04,673
ln a place far, far away
there lives an old woman

681
00:55:33,840 --> 00:55:35,796
Catch this.

682
00:55:39,160 --> 00:55:42,357
- l got you there.
- You're evil.

683
00:55:46,560 --> 00:55:48,755
Don't worry, l'm here.

684
00:55:48,840 --> 00:55:51,035
No, go and see why the light went out.

685
00:55:51,120 --> 00:55:54,157
Don't you think a dark world
for two people is romantic?

686
00:55:54,240 --> 00:55:57,516
No. lf there's no power,
food in the fridge will spoil,

687
00:55:57,600 --> 00:56:01,513
our rice and soup will all be half cooked,
there's still something in the oven...

688
00:56:01,600 --> 00:56:04,637
- Go and see what happened.
- l'm no generator.

689
00:56:04,720 --> 00:56:06,915
l can't help even if l know what happened.

690
00:56:11,480 --> 00:56:13,232
lt's not short-circuited.

691
00:56:25,600 --> 00:56:27,158
Who is it?

692
00:56:31,680 --> 00:56:33,318
Jackie?

693
00:56:34,440 --> 00:56:35,634
What happened?

694
00:56:42,680 --> 00:56:44,318
Jackie, what happened?

695
00:56:45,560 --> 00:56:48,757
- Someone is trying to harm us.
- What should we do?

696
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:52,958
Go to the sitting room with this,
count to three and turn it on.

697
00:56:53,040 --> 00:56:56,271
- But...
- Go now, quickly.

698
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:07,355
Jackie, l've turned it on. What next?

699
00:57:07,440 --> 00:57:09,237
Be careful.

700
00:57:20,760 --> 00:57:22,751
What? Tung Te-Biu?

701
00:57:26,640 --> 00:57:28,358
- Have you gone mad?
- l'm not mad.

702
00:57:28,440 --> 00:57:31,989
- Do you know what you're doing?
- Yes, getting rid of a witness.

703
00:57:38,880 --> 00:57:41,348
- Let me go.
- Cousin!

704
00:57:41,440 --> 00:57:44,591
- Cut it out. What happened?
- None of your business.

705
00:57:44,680 --> 00:57:46,989
- You're so rude.
- l'm better than you.

706
00:57:47,080 --> 00:57:49,674
You just wanted her to sell the fish farm.

707
00:57:50,720 --> 00:57:52,915
What did he just say?

708
00:57:53,000 --> 00:57:54,911
Nothing, he's lying.

709
00:57:55,720 --> 00:57:58,029
- Stop fighting.
- Stop fighting.

710
00:57:58,120 --> 00:57:59,473
Stop, stop.

711
00:58:00,760 --> 00:58:02,990
- l can explain.
- Don't listen to him.

712
00:58:03,080 --> 00:58:06,072
- Shut up.
- You shut up, it's all your fault.

713
00:58:06,160 --> 00:58:10,278
You asked me to bug her house.
She's suing me and you don't care.

714
00:58:10,360 --> 00:58:14,558
- You're despicable.
- Don't listen to him. He's lying.

715
00:58:16,400 --> 00:58:17,469
Listen to me.

716
00:58:17,560 --> 00:58:20,836
Ah Ling, let me explain,
things are not as complex as you thought.

717
00:58:20,920 --> 00:58:24,117
- lt's a simple matter.
- lt's really simple.

718
00:58:24,200 --> 00:58:26,156
Get out of my sight.

719
00:58:28,640 --> 00:58:31,154
Ah Ling. Let me explain.

720
00:58:31,240 --> 00:58:34,357
- Explain in court.
- Ah Ling!

721
00:58:37,040 --> 00:58:38,678
Ah Ling.

722
00:58:40,880 --> 00:58:42,233
You've ruined everything.

723
00:58:42,320 --> 00:58:45,630
lt was ruined the minute
he caught me bugging the house.

724
00:58:45,720 --> 00:58:48,473
l've told you, right? lt was a mistake.

725
00:58:48,560 --> 00:58:51,472
- See who you hired.
- Hey, Ah Biu...

726
00:58:51,560 --> 00:58:54,996
Enough... l can only depend on myself.

727
00:58:55,080 --> 00:58:58,470
l know that this is a world without love.

728
00:58:59,840 --> 00:59:01,512
l said l would help you win the case.

729
00:59:01,600 --> 00:59:04,068
Win the case? You can't even win my trust.

730
00:59:04,160 --> 00:59:06,833
- You two are useless.
- Haven't you had enough?

731
00:59:06,920 --> 00:59:10,276
Are you taking it out on me? Come on.

732
00:59:10,360 --> 00:59:12,999
- Don't push me so hard.
- l can't control...

733
00:59:17,120 --> 00:59:20,351
- Big nose, you hit me?
- Any time.

734
00:59:22,160 --> 00:59:24,151
And l can hit you any time.

735
00:59:51,280 --> 00:59:56,195
We've called the police.
Keep on fighting, if you dare.

736
01:00:12,920 --> 01:00:19,473
l've used all the tricks available to get
the Commisioner to drop the charges.

737
01:00:19,560 --> 01:00:22,472
The three of you are too
old to fight in the street.

738
01:00:22,560 --> 01:00:24,516
Excuse me.

739
01:00:31,240 --> 01:00:33,595
Why were you fighting? Over women?

740
01:00:36,760 --> 01:00:40,639
The skinny one fought over two women.
The fatty did it over a woman.

741
01:00:40,720 --> 01:00:43,359
l did it over two men.

742
01:00:49,440 --> 01:00:53,752
l got up early in the morning to get
you off the hook, what's my reward?

743
01:01:02,280 --> 01:01:03,838
What do you say?

744
01:01:05,560 --> 01:01:07,357
l'm lovelorn.

745
01:01:07,440 --> 01:01:10,432
lf it was me you loved,
you wouldn't be lovelorn.

746
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:21,155
We've lost a lot of fish.
What should we do now?

747
01:01:21,240 --> 01:01:23,629
That factory is manufacturing illegal drugs.

748
01:01:31,200 --> 01:01:33,111
l don't believe you will stay there.

749
01:01:33,200 --> 01:01:35,350
l don't believe you're not hitting the brake.

750
01:01:38,680 --> 01:01:40,716
A good dog would not block the way.

751
01:01:40,800 --> 01:01:42,392
- l'm not a good dog.
- Nor a good man.

752
01:01:42,480 --> 01:01:44,869
- l'm a good man.
- You're a love cheat.

753
01:01:44,960 --> 01:01:47,349
l didn't cheat you.
l invested emotionally as well.

754
01:01:47,440 --> 01:01:49,396
- Really?
- Can't you feel it?

755
01:01:49,480 --> 01:01:51,710
No, l've no feelings for you.

756
01:01:54,280 --> 01:01:56,191
You wasted my time and emotion.

757
01:01:56,280 --> 01:01:59,113
For a bit of commission,
you betrayed me and yourself.

758
01:02:07,600 --> 01:02:11,559
- Why didn't you dodge?
- l wouldn't have come if l wanted to dodge.

759
01:02:15,880 --> 01:02:18,678
- That was too risky.
- But not enough to kill him.

760
01:02:18,760 --> 01:02:23,151
l was talking about you.
lf he got hold of the spanner, we'd be dead.

761
01:02:23,240 --> 01:02:25,515
l'm not like that. Please let me explain.

762
01:02:25,600 --> 01:02:28,433
lnitially, l did get
close to you for the commission.

763
01:02:28,520 --> 01:02:32,035
After spending some time together,
l realise that l've fallen for you.

764
01:02:32,120 --> 01:02:33,872
You just wanted to be
the boss of a fish farm.

765
01:02:33,960 --> 01:02:38,158
lt did cross my mind,
but to prove my true love for you,

766
01:02:38,240 --> 01:02:41,789
you can sell the farm
for charity before marrying me.

767
01:02:42,840 --> 01:02:45,400
Sell the farm for charity?
Are we going to live on air?

768
01:02:45,480 --> 01:02:48,756
l don't mind living on air.
As long as we don't have to live on shit.

769
01:02:48,840 --> 01:02:51,912
Even if l don't sell the farm,
we'll have to live on air.

770
01:02:52,000 --> 01:02:54,719
The factory kept dumping
waste water into our farm.

771
01:02:54,800 --> 01:02:56,916
l'll check what they're doing in the factory.

772
01:02:57,000 --> 01:02:58,877
- Get in the car, then.
- Yes.

773
01:03:00,200 --> 01:03:02,156
Hey, why are you so obedient?

774
01:03:03,960 --> 01:03:06,758
- Let's go, then.
- OK.

775
01:03:15,040 --> 01:03:16,996
Your friend is here.

776
01:03:27,160 --> 01:03:31,312
- Ah Ling.
- Say nothing, save it for the court.

777
01:03:33,560 --> 01:03:36,028
- Take care.
- OK.

778
01:03:38,080 --> 01:03:40,799
l want to help you but l can't.

779
01:03:41,360 --> 01:03:44,033
l don't mean any harm, l just wanted
you to drop the case against me.

780
01:03:44,120 --> 01:03:48,750
l'll drop the case
if you promise not to stalk me.

781
01:03:48,840 --> 01:03:51,673
That is not a problem. l'm on my way.

782
01:03:55,360 --> 01:03:57,316
Why are they against me and not you?

783
01:03:57,400 --> 01:03:59,834
That's the power of love.

784
01:04:01,440 --> 01:04:03,954
- Hey, do something for me?
- OK.

785
01:04:04,040 --> 01:04:06,190
- l can't pay.
- l don't mind.

786
01:04:06,280 --> 01:04:08,236
Come with me.

787
01:04:25,760 --> 01:04:27,830
Hey...

788
01:04:27,920 --> 01:04:30,639
- Hey, you don't have to act like that.
- l'm being cautious.

789
01:04:32,200 --> 01:04:36,079
We'll split up now
and meet here in 20 minutes.

790
01:04:39,680 --> 01:04:42,194
l've got you in shot
to prove that you're working.

791
01:05:25,080 --> 01:05:26,035
Follow me.

792
01:06:32,520 --> 01:06:34,476
What kind of factory is this?

793
01:07:12,400 --> 01:07:17,155
How do you do?
Sorry to interrupt, l'm going now.

794
01:07:17,240 --> 01:07:19,310
Bye-bye, see you later.

795
01:07:23,840 --> 01:07:25,910
How is everybody doing?

796
01:07:28,200 --> 01:07:30,475
- What's this?
- Nothing - a telescope.

797
01:07:30,560 --> 01:07:32,278
- Give it back.
- Get him.

798
01:07:32,360 --> 01:07:34,237
Don't move. You can't touch me.

799
01:07:35,760 --> 01:07:37,955
Fatty. How did you get in?

800
01:07:38,040 --> 01:07:39,598
Hi, how are you?

801
01:07:57,680 --> 01:07:58,669
Don't move.

802
01:08:02,200 --> 01:08:04,430
Don't let him escape.

803
01:08:04,520 --> 01:08:07,159
OK, go for broke.

804
01:08:21,760 --> 01:08:23,318
Get him.

805
01:09:08,040 --> 01:09:11,032
Calm down, everyone,
that's the end of him.

806
01:09:15,000 --> 01:09:17,036
Tie him up.

807
01:09:17,120 --> 01:09:20,556
District Court civil case number 2346.

808
01:09:20,640 --> 01:09:26,431
The Yip Fish Farm is applying for an
injunction against Wah Chemical Works

809
01:09:26,520 --> 01:09:28,272
for continuing production.

810
01:09:28,360 --> 01:09:30,794
The court will be presided over by Judge Lo.

811
01:09:38,760 --> 01:09:40,910
Let me go. Why are you tying me up?

812
01:10:01,880 --> 01:10:03,552
lf he wakes up, give him another jab.

813
01:10:14,560 --> 01:10:16,516
Stupid Fatty.

814
01:10:17,680 --> 01:10:21,753
Since l'm related to the plaintiff
and to show my impartiality in the case,

815
01:10:21,840 --> 01:10:24,434
l've entrusted all specimen tests

816
01:10:24,520 --> 01:10:28,274
to the Hong Kong University
Oceanography Department.

817
01:10:28,360 --> 01:10:31,352
The results show that
the lead content in the water

818
01:10:31,440 --> 01:10:33,476
is two per cent higher than normal.

819
01:10:33,560 --> 01:10:35,790
And the oxygen is three per cent
lower than the standard.

820
01:10:51,240 --> 01:10:54,710
Thank you, Miss Wen.
Your Honour, no more questions.

821
01:11:08,720 --> 01:11:12,156
Defence counsel, this is a civil case.

822
01:11:12,240 --> 01:11:15,118
The statements given
by the witnesses are professional.

823
01:11:15,200 --> 01:11:19,876
l advise you not to use the usual
psychological tactics in your argument.

824
01:11:19,960 --> 01:11:21,916
Yes, Your Honour.

825
01:11:33,480 --> 01:11:38,600
Miss Wen, before you started
giving your statements,

826
01:11:38,680 --> 01:11:42,719
you vowed to speak nothing but the truth,
is that right?

827
01:11:42,800 --> 01:11:44,950
- l've not forgotten.
- Miss Wen Mei Ling,

828
01:11:45,040 --> 01:11:48,396
please answer
the following question sincerely.

829
01:11:51,400 --> 01:11:53,356
Do you love me?

830
01:11:55,240 --> 01:11:57,549
Can he ask that?

831
01:11:58,240 --> 01:12:00,834
- Objection. That's irrelevant.
- Objection overruled.

832
01:12:00,920 --> 01:12:03,718
- None of your business.
- What happened?

833
01:12:03,800 --> 01:12:06,598
lt's up to me to overrule any objections.

834
01:12:08,360 --> 01:12:12,148
Defence counsel, please explain
the relevance of this question.

835
01:12:12,240 --> 01:12:14,629
l'm sorry, Your Honour.

836
01:12:14,720 --> 01:12:17,996
Please believe that l have
sufficient reason to ask the question.

837
01:12:18,080 --> 01:12:22,153
l'll explain after the witness
has answered the question sincerely.

838
01:12:24,120 --> 01:12:26,839
Miss Wen, do you love him?

839
01:12:26,920 --> 01:12:29,832
Your Honour, can we talk
about the water quality?

840
01:12:29,920 --> 01:12:31,990
l'm testifying as an oceanography expert.

841
01:12:32,080 --> 01:12:35,117
l know you're an oceanography expert.

842
01:12:35,200 --> 01:12:38,875
You're not only an expert,
you're also a woman.

843
01:12:38,960 --> 01:12:43,158
The court would only object to a man
asking another man about love,

844
01:12:43,240 --> 01:12:45,276
because that's abnormal.

845
01:12:45,360 --> 01:12:49,831
As to a man asking a woman
whether she loves him,

846
01:12:49,920 --> 01:12:51,319
it's perfectly normal.

847
01:12:51,400 --> 01:12:53,960
lt's not illegal, either.

848
01:12:54,760 --> 01:12:58,719
l can't find a reason to object
to him asking this question.

849
01:12:58,800 --> 01:13:01,030
So you must answer his question.

850
01:13:01,120 --> 01:13:05,113
Your Honour, l don't wish to discuss
my love life in the court.

851
01:13:05,200 --> 01:13:09,637
l disagree. The Court insists.

852
01:13:10,480 --> 01:13:11,799
Do you love me?

853
01:13:13,480 --> 01:13:15,277
You have to answer this.

854
01:13:19,440 --> 01:13:21,396
l don't.

855
01:13:24,320 --> 01:13:28,598
Making a false statement is an act
of contempt of court. Did you know that?

856
01:13:29,240 --> 01:13:32,915
He might sound a bit threatening
but it's true.

857
01:13:33,000 --> 01:13:37,551
Sorry, Your Honour. l might be a bit harsh
but this question is very important to me.

858
01:13:37,640 --> 01:13:40,791
lt's right for young people
to take love seriously.

859
01:13:40,880 --> 01:13:44,998
Miss Wen, please think
twice before answering.

860
01:13:45,840 --> 01:13:49,435
- Do you love me or not?
- Why are you forcing me?

861
01:13:49,520 --> 01:13:52,114
An oath taken outside
the court means nothing.

862
01:13:52,200 --> 01:13:55,636
lnside the court, it's legally binding.

863
01:13:55,720 --> 01:13:58,439
To lie in court is a criminal act.

864
01:13:58,520 --> 01:14:02,149
l want to know for real
whether you love me or not.

865
01:14:02,240 --> 01:14:05,596
The answer you give will not only
affect my work in the future,

866
01:14:05,680 --> 01:14:08,513
it'll determine the course of my life.

867
01:14:08,600 --> 01:14:11,273
Sentimental men like you are rare.

868
01:14:11,360 --> 01:14:15,239
l'm a judge, l decide
who's wrong and who's right.

869
01:14:15,320 --> 01:14:17,959
But l can't decide
whether he's the one for you.

870
01:14:18,040 --> 01:14:21,112
You'll be the judge
of this case within a case.

871
01:14:21,200 --> 01:14:23,760
We're waiting for your verdict.

872
01:14:27,080 --> 01:14:28,149
l...

873
01:14:29,160 --> 01:14:31,196
love him.

874
01:14:39,520 --> 01:14:41,590
Your Honour, since we're in love

875
01:14:41,680 --> 01:14:45,070
and she and l are representing the plaintiff
and the defendent respectively,

876
01:14:45,160 --> 01:14:48,197
for impartiality and
in the interests of both parties,

877
01:14:48,280 --> 01:14:50,840
one of us has to withdraw from the case.

878
01:14:50,920 --> 01:14:54,117
Your Honour, please allow my withdrawal.

879
01:14:57,320 --> 01:15:01,029
Permission granted. Hearing adjourned.

880
01:15:03,080 --> 01:15:05,230
Court!

881
01:15:09,080 --> 01:15:10,991
- lncompetent service.
- Stupid man.

882
01:15:26,960 --> 01:15:31,397
Since you didn't give me the chance
to say it, l said it all in court.

883
01:15:33,440 --> 01:15:34,429
Keep the change.

884
01:15:38,520 --> 01:15:41,193
- l'm sorry to interrupt, but l've no choice.
- What happened?

885
01:15:49,000 --> 01:15:52,356
- Excuse me.
- What happened?

886
01:15:52,440 --> 01:15:56,069
- Nothing. Go home, l'll come round later.
- Let's go.

887
01:15:57,240 --> 01:16:00,277
Get a cab for yourself.
l've something to attend to.

888
01:16:05,720 --> 01:16:07,676
Hey.

889
01:16:24,000 --> 01:16:25,956
Boss.

890
01:16:29,560 --> 01:16:32,870
This is where we started,
he went that way and l...

891
01:16:32,960 --> 01:16:34,837
- Wait for me here.
- No.

892
01:16:34,920 --> 01:16:37,036
- lt's dangerous inside.
- l'm not afraid.

893
01:16:37,120 --> 01:16:39,395
- l can't take care of you.
- l'll be all right.

894
01:16:39,480 --> 01:16:41,357
- Are you clear?
- Yes. Let's go.

895
01:16:49,040 --> 01:16:50,996
- Put this on.
- Why?

896
01:16:51,080 --> 01:16:52,149
You'll see later.

897
01:17:03,520 --> 01:17:04,509
Ah Biu...

898
01:17:07,080 --> 01:17:09,389
- Be careful.
- You too.

899
01:17:14,040 --> 01:17:16,713
- Hey, be careful.
- l will.

900
01:17:48,000 --> 01:17:49,911
- Dump him into the sea.
- Yes.

901
01:17:52,160 --> 01:17:53,115
'Hey.'

902
01:17:59,120 --> 01:18:00,269
Don't move.

903
01:18:00,360 --> 01:18:02,510
- We're looking for someone.
- What?

904
01:18:02,600 --> 01:18:04,556
We're looking for someone.

905
01:18:05,880 --> 01:18:07,632
Whoever you're looking for isn't here.

906
01:18:07,720 --> 01:18:11,395
He's here. We came together
and l've not seen him since.

907
01:18:11,480 --> 01:18:13,311
He must be here, we can't be wrong.

908
01:18:13,400 --> 01:18:14,753
Shut up.

909
01:18:14,840 --> 01:18:18,355
The court might be your territory
but this is mine. l want you out.

910
01:18:18,440 --> 01:18:21,671
We mustn't be rash. Let's go.

911
01:18:27,720 --> 01:18:29,711
They're producing illegal drugs here.

912
01:18:29,800 --> 01:18:31,279
Get rid of him.

913
01:18:43,880 --> 01:18:47,190
- l said l can't take care of you.
- l said l'll be all right.

914
01:19:09,840 --> 01:19:11,990
l don't believe l can't deal with you.

915
01:19:51,960 --> 01:19:53,871
Wong Fei-Hung, how are you doing?

916
01:19:53,960 --> 01:19:55,916
l'm very high.

917
01:22:13,160 --> 01:22:15,116
Bastard.

918
01:22:36,520 --> 01:22:41,071
Get rid of him
and you'll have half the factory.

919
01:22:41,160 --> 01:22:42,798
Leave it to me.

920
01:24:06,040 --> 01:24:06,995
ldiot.

921
01:25:29,360 --> 01:25:32,079
- Wong Fei-Hung, are you all right?
- Not really.

922
01:25:32,880 --> 01:25:34,836
- Call the police.
- OK.

923
01:25:48,240 --> 01:25:51,710
Bitch! How dare you upset my production!

924
01:26:02,800 --> 01:26:05,758
Jackie, Jackie.

925
01:26:10,960 --> 01:26:12,234
My hand hurts.

926
01:26:13,600 --> 01:26:15,556
That's the point.

927
01:26:23,960 --> 01:26:25,552
Trying to poison me?

928
01:26:57,040 --> 01:26:59,600
Goodbye, my friend.

929
01:28:26,200 --> 01:28:27,155
Ah Ling.

930
01:28:31,640 --> 01:28:33,915
Does it still hurt?

931
01:28:34,000 --> 01:28:35,911
- No.
- Didn't l tell you not to come?

932
01:28:36,000 --> 01:28:38,468
- l was worried about you.
- Don't do that again.

933
01:28:38,560 --> 01:28:41,358
The love birds are mooning
and you're moaning.

934
01:28:41,440 --> 01:28:44,079
Can you wake up, please?

935
01:28:44,160 --> 01:28:46,913
Why didn't you tell me you were here?
What happened?

936
01:28:47,000 --> 01:28:47,989
lt was...

937
01:28:48,080 --> 01:28:49,195
Sweetheart.

938
01:28:50,200 --> 01:28:51,553
Darling.

939
01:28:57,840 --> 01:28:58,795
Love over friends.

940
01:29:07,200 --> 01:29:11,671
A warm feeling rushes to my ears

941
01:29:11,760 --> 01:29:15,799
A cupid's arrow

942
01:29:15,880 --> 01:29:24,629
is turning in my heart

943
01:29:24,720 --> 01:29:28,918
A gentle touch joins us together

944
01:29:29,000 --> 01:29:33,790
and sets my heart racing

945
01:29:33,880 --> 01:29:41,230
My love will bring you warmth and joy

946
01:29:44,200 --> 01:29:48,637
Happiness in your heart will rise and grow

947
01:29:48,720 --> 01:29:52,793
The warmth you feel will never fade

948
01:29:52,880 --> 01:29:59,433
When our hearts are joined

949
01:30:02,040 --> 01:30:06,318
Happiness in your heart will rise and grow

950
01:30:06,400 --> 01:30:10,837
The warmth you feel will never fade

951
01:30:10,920 --> 01:30:17,359
Love is like an electric current

